The goals of the School-to-Careers System shall be to:
Increase the math, science, communications, social studies, and technical skills of all students through the implementation of a more rigorous and relevant applied curriculum and instructional process;
Increase the awareness of job and career availability in the future workforce and the skills required to obtain those positions;
Increase the postsecondary education's entry and completion rates and reduce the percentage of students taking remedial courses;
Decrease the high school dropout rate through a system of increased guidance and extra help focused on academics and career achievement;
Make all students aware of employer expectations in order to be successful;
Increase the daily attendance rate at all secondary schools; and
Provide the educational experiences that will cause all students to meet the goals and capacities identified in KRS 158.645 and KRS 158.6451 for Kentucky students.
